The paper discusses a new approach for scientific computing that involves remote function execution on existing infrastructure, which is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, the paper focuses on high-performance function-as-a-service (FaaS) platform, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel computing (cs.SC). The paper also discusses the need for new design approaches in which monolithic applications can be decomposed into smaller components, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Overall, the paper is likely to be classified under cs.DC as it primarily focuses on distributed computing and parallel processing.
